Pre-Game Insights: Willy Sagnol dismissed rumors of leaving for another job, stating he expects to be working for Georgia for 'the next few years'

Czechia manager Ivan Hašek provided a fitness update on a couple of key players. He revealed that star striker Patrik Schick was only withdrawn on the hour mark because he was tracking back so much and beginning to tire. Tomáš Souček, meanwhile, had to undergo treatment ahead of Czechia’s opener but is not feeling any great discomfort and is happy to keep playing.
Miscellaneous Highlights: This marks the first-ever coming together of these two nations.
Others: The match will take place on June 22, 2024, at the Volksparkstadion in Hamburg, Germany. The kick-off time is 15:00 CEST (14:00 BST). The referee for the match is Daniel Siebert (GER) and the VAR is Marco Fritz (GER).
In the UK, BBC One is the channel you need to watch the match. In Czechia, viewers can watch live via Česká Televize (CT) Sport. In Georgia, the game will be accessible via 1TV (aka First Channel).
